metadata.name: Dragon Fire II #79
metadata.description:
Each Dragon Fire design is painted from a random 100 color gradient on a 3200x3200 canvas using p5js. This version includes performance optimizations including an "edge pixel" algorithm that allows for a much higher resolution painting that renders over 10 million pixels in a fraction of the time compared to the original.

While this version is far more performant, it is resource intensive and might not work on all browsers. It was developed on the latest version of Chrome and tested on Firefox, Safari, and Brave.

metadata.name: Omega Point #225
metadata.description:
In the collapsing universe approaching singularity, the last remaining cybernetic organisms encounter the state of infinite knowledge, information, and computational resources.
Although the living creatures in the Omega Point are destined for imminent destruction, they experience infinite life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'space' - improve image quality
'f' - increase rendering speed

The image quality gradually improves over time, up to a certain level. To reach the maximum quality, press 'space'.
The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
Requires WebGL2.

metadata.name: stigmergy #179
metadata.description:
Stigmergy is a method of decentralized organization in which agents communicate by leaving traces in a shared environment. This piece simulates a kind of stigmergy among a large population of particles. Each particle leaves a trail behind it as it moves, and determines its direction of motion based on the trails around it. The rules for how a particle should move based on its surroundings were created with a user-guided evolutionary process.

Press "c" to capture a 2048x2048 image of the simulation. You can also press the spacebar to pause/unpause the simulation, and press "n" while paused to move the simulation forward a single step.

metadata.name: We're not gonna take it! #3
metadata.description:
Wake up, get up, get out there and fight for your right to party!
Energy, youth, rebellion, hope, and a pinch of horniness.

Click/Tap & Drag your mouse/finger around to slightly rotate the viewport.

High contrast arrows on vibrant colors.
Everything procedural and generated at runtime. Your hash determines some general characteritics for the arrows shape wich then have each their own uniqueness. Black concentric shapes come in the background to reinforce the directional feel.
Made fully in 3D, with the intent to simulate the feel of 2D stencil graffiti. The black shapes in the background are for instance just three deformed spheres with some intense cell shading plus some tricks to add some accidents.

Developped and released specifically for fxhash 1.0 reopening, the mood mirroring the energy, dynamism and generally positive feelings of the community.
As it happens on Easter/Pesach weekend, I had to include easter eggs.

Kind of an hommage to the UI work of Masayoshi Sutoh for Persona 5

Press space on your keyboard to show/hide a menu with :
- An option to mirror the piece horizontally if your culture associates progress with a right to left mouvement rather than the opposite
- Export a capture by choossing a size in pixels in the dropdown and pressing the big button.

GPU Recommended, but it's pretty light. Should run fine in most case, even on mobile (without super sampling tough).

Happy FXHash Fest!

metadata.name: Ray Drops #7
metadata.description:
Ray Drops plays with the idea of rays that are projected out from a random center point which oscillate at variable frequencies. At each inflection point it has a chance of being intersected by a ring. The inflection points vary in how closely they are spaced and can cluster around the center point or fan all the way out to the edges. 

When run this generative creates a 12 layer SVG vector that is designed to be run on a laser cutter in order to build an in real life woodcut. Each layer is a single contiguous piece with no floating elements so when cut out of wood you end up with 12 layers that can be secured with 10 Chicago screws.  

Learn more and get physical editions: https://alleditions.art/p/ray-drops

Shift P - exports a PNG
Shift S - exports SVG
Shift E - explodes the layers

The 5 rarest mints (once the series is minted out) will receive a free signed physical which can be claimed by an owner of the NFT at anytime. It can be left attached and claimed by any future owner. 

I will also be giving away 5 free signed physicals randomly to people who tweet a picture of their edition and tag @shawnkemp
